AGENDA.Definition: the underlying intentions or motives of a particular person or group

ASPIRATIONAL.Definition: having or characterized by aspirations to achieve social prestige and material success

BLOSSOM.Definition: mature or develop in a promising or healthy way

DIVIDENDS.Definition: a benefit from an action or policy

DOMINANT.Definition: having power and influence over others

FOOTPRINT.Definition: the impression left by a foot or shoe on the ground or a surface

FOSTER.Definition: encourage the development of (something, especially something desirable)

IMPRINT.Definition: make an impression or mark on

INSTITUTIONS.Definition: an established official organization having an important role in a society, such as the Church or parliament

LINGUA FRANCA.Definition: a language that is adopted as a common language between speakers whose native languages are different

MASTERY.Definition: comprehensive knowledge or skill in a particular subject or activity

PROJECT.Definition: present or promote (a particular view or image)

PROJECTED.Definition: present or promote (a particular view or image)

REAPING.Definition: receive (something, especially something beneficial) as a consequence of one's own or another's actions

SANCTIONS.Definition: a threatened penalty for disobeying a law or rule

SELF-PROCLAIMED.Definition: described as or proclaimed to be such by oneself, without endorsement by others

SHIFT.Definition: a slight change in position, direction, or tendency.: 'a shift in public opinion' 'a shift of wind took us by surprise'.

SLIPPED.Definition: pass or change to a lower, worse, or different condition, typically in a gradual or imperceptible way

SOUNDBITES.Definition: a short extract from a recorded interview or speech, chosen for its succinctness or concision
